The first mmt was collected at the normal mmt section 70 m d/s where there was there was 4 m of shore ice on the RB and small amounts of ice on the rocks in the mmt section.  the second mmt was completed 2 m d/s of the bridge between the rocky debris that constrict the channel at lower flows.  mmt section was 99% open.  WL was observed to be pulsing up down +/- 0.05m on the wading rod during the mmt.  Velocity in the middle of the section was observed at .3 m/s and then up to .6 m/s during a pulse of faster flow.  approx 3 mins of increased flow to 3 mins of decreased flow.  Velocities may be suspect for the mmt.
